Imaging features of sarcoidosis on MDCT, FDG PET, and PET/CT. The objectives of this article are to discuss the epidemiology and natural history of sarcoidosis to review the classic imaging features of sarcoidosis on radiography, CT, and 67Ga nuclear medicine scansThe imaging features of sarcoidosis are diverse and can be seen on a variety of imaging techniques. It is important for radiologists and nuclear medicine physicians to recognize the common imaging features and patterns of sarcoidosis in order to raise the possibility in the appropriate clinical setting.